REF. NO.: RPB/NSL/2026/001
Date: 15.01.2026

To,
The Managing Director,
Rajasthan Medical Services Corporation Ltd.,
Jaipur – 302 015

Sub: Formal Record of No Satisfaction and Invocation of Arbitration Clause
     Re: Construction of 300-Bed Hospital Udaipur — W.O. No. RMSCL/2024-25/Works/4782

Sir,

1. Reference is made to our Legal Notice dated 12.12.2025 and the Standing Committee Meeting held on 08.01.2026.

2. Despite our Legal Notice, RMSCL has failed to:
   a) Release the withheld running bills of ₹12.45 Crore.
   b) Grant Extension of Time for employer-caused delays.
   c) Issue formal Variation Orders for extra work executed on Engineer's instructions.

3. The Standing Committee Meeting of 08.01.2026 has recommended termination without addressing our grievances.

4. We hereby formally record our NO SATISFACTION with the decision of the Employer.

5. In accordance with Clause 25 of CPWD GCC 2020 read with Section 11(6) of the Arbitration & Conciliation Act, 1996,
   we hereby INVOKE ARBITRATION for resolution of all disputes.

6. We request RMSCL to name their nominee arbitrator within 30 days failing which we shall approach
   Hon'ble High Court of Rajasthan for appointment of Sole Arbitrator.

Yours faithfully,

For M/s. Rajputana Builders Pvt. Ltd.
Director / Authorized Signatory
